BBK01.WT5006: Exchange rates on the Frankfurt exchange /ESP 100 = DM ... / Spain

General: Spot middle rates in Deutsche Mark; difference between buying or selling rate and middle rate in D-Mark: 0.010 up to the end of August 1978 / 0.005 up to the end of 1993 / 0.0040 since 1994. From 18 February 1963 to 30 December 1998 official quotation on the Frankfurt exchange. In accordance with a resolution by the management board of the Frankfurt exchange, with effect from January 1994 the exchange rate of the Peseta was set at four decimal places. For technical reasons, the exchange rates up to December 1993 were extended from three to four decimal places. From 1 January 1999, irrevocable euro conversion rate: Euro 1 = Ptas 166.386. Our specific comments refer to "Frankfurt exchange closed on ..." (Devisenbrse am ... geschlossen) or "Quotation suspended on ..." (Notierung am ... ausgesetzt).
